title: Grateful Dead Live at Auditorium Theatre on 1976-06-29
taper: Betty Cantor, provided by Rich Gastwirt
description:
Set 1

Tennessee Jed, Cassidy, Peggy-O, Mama Tried, Mission In The Rain, Looks Like Rain, Brown Eyed Women, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Row Jimmy, The Music Never Stopped, Might As Well

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Candyman, Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Playin' In The Band-> Saint Stephen-> Not Fade Away-> Saint Stephen-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

FM Broadcast WXRT

reviews.review_text: Fantastic Show and Sound Quality Ive admitted elsewhere, and will here again, that I'd always slept on the '76 shows, preferring '77 and a few other years / periods. What a mistake. I believe if you really like '74 for example, this is the progression of, or maybe the finished product of what started in '73 / '74. Another great June show right here with it's own vibe. As with the other recent Betty / Dalton / Clugston / Miller additions here, you know these names and what they can do. No disrespect to the J Ashley / Bertha here, which is also great, but this deserves your listening pleasure..it's truly of the highest quality stuff on here.
Worth a Second Listen... What a high energy, amazing set list, great sounding 1976 "Betty Board" show! Not much else to say, just enjoy it.
